for test in OBD_data.keys():

            OBD_data[test][car].loc[:, 'Vehicle speed (km/h)'] = 1.60934 * OBD_data[test][car]["Vehicle speed (MPH)"]
            OBD_data[test][car]["Fuel rate (l/hr)"] = 3.78541 * OBD_data[test][car]["Fuel rate (gal/hr)"]

            print(test, car)

        start_time[test][car] = OBD_data[test][car].iloc[np.min(np.where(OBD_data[test][car].loc[:,"Vehicle speed (km/h)"] > 0)),0]

Synchronisation by minimising least sum of square errors¶

In [402]:
# Do linear interpolation from OBD times to camera times (30 Hz), 
# then find the optimal start time which minimises sum of square errors between
# OBD velocities and camera speeds.

start_time_optimal = {}
search_range = 50    # search range +/- 50 secs from pre-determined start time

for test in OBD_data.keys():
    start_time_optimal[test] = {}

    for car in OBD_data[test].keys():
        # search OBD times +/- 50 secs from pre-determined start time
        times_to_test = OBD_data[test][car].iloc[:,0].between(start_time[test][car] - search_range/2,
                                                             start_time[test][car] + search_range/2)
        times_to_test = OBD_data[test][car].iloc[:,0][times_to_test]
        
        results_sse = []
        for times in times_to_test:
            # Interpolate the OBD times to match the time intervals from the camera (30 Hz)
            OBD_vel_interp = np.interp(x = np.linspace(times, times+test_durations[test], test_durations[test]*30),
                                       xp = OBD_data[test][car]["Time (sec)"],
                                       fp = OBD_data[test][car].loc[:,"Vehicle speed (km/h)"]*1000/3600)
            
            # calculate sum of square errors between OBD velocities and camera speeds, store the value
            results_sse.append(np.sum((OBD_vel_interp-camera_data[test]['velocities_regularized'][car-1][:,0])**2))
        
        # Get the start time that minimises sse.
        start_time_optimal[test][car] = times_to_test.iloc[np.argmin(results_sse)]
        
        # Plot sse against start times
        plt.plot(times_to_test, results_sse)
        plt.axvline(start_time_optimal[test][car], color="red")
        plt.title("test "+test+", car "+str(car))
        plt.ylabel("Sum of Square Errors")
        plt.xlabel("Start Time")
        plt.show()

Plot the matched OBD and camera data using the optimal start times¶

In [385]:
for test in OBD_data.keys():
    for car in OBD_data[test].keys():
        plt.plot(OBD_data[test][car]["Time (sec)"] - start_time_optimal[test][car], 
                 OBD_data[test][car].loc[:,"Vehicle speed (km/h)"]*1000/3600, color='blue', linewidth=0.5)
        plt.plot(np.arange(0, test_durations[test], 1/30), 
                 camera_data[test]['velocities_regularized'][car-1][:,0], color='red')
        plt.xlim(0)
        plt.xlabel("Time (s)")
        plt.ylabel("Velocity (m/s)")
        plt.title("test "+test+", car "+str(car))
        plt.ylim(0)
        plt.show()

Get mean fuel rates (l/hr)¶

In [393]:
print ("Mean Fuel Rates (l/hr)")
for test in OBD_data.keys():
    print("\nTest", test)
    for car in OBD_data[test].keys():
        print("Car", car,
              round(np.mean(OBD_data[test][car]["Fuel rate (l/hr)"]
                      [OBD_data[test][car].iloc[:,0].between(start_time_optimal[test][car], 
                                                                        start_time_optimal[test][car]+test_durations[test])]), 
                    2))
